      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NO NOTTHEBUTTONS (7) rises in grade but has looked good in easily winning his three starts since joining Seaton Grima. Came from this same barrier last time, racing parked before drawing right away to salute by close to 10m at this circuit. Can take this next step. There was plenty to like about the latest performance of DESSIE GEE (4) when he came from wider for a 1.4m second in a handy line-up. That continued a run of top-four results and he should get his chance from this draw. ISLA ROCHELLE (8) missed the placings as favourite at Wagga last week but had scored twice in a row here prior, part of a long string of win and placings. Can bounce back. MIKE ROSS NZ (5) and ALTA SIERRA (6) have been thereabouts of late and can be competitive.",
